# Contacts API Testing
# Use with REST Client extension in VS Code

### 1. Get all contacts (with pagination)
GET http://localhost:3000/api/contacts?page=1&limit=10

### 2. Get contacts filtered by status
GET http://localhost:3000/api/contacts?status=new&page=1&limit=10

### 3. Get contact statistics
GET http://localhost:3000/api/contacts/stats

### 4. Create new contact (minimal required fields)
POST http://localhost:3000/api/contacts
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "full_name": "John Doe",
  "phone": "+1234567890"
}

### 5. Create contact with all fields
POST http://localhost:3000/api/contacts
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "full_name": "Jane Smith",
  "phone": "0987654321",
  "email": "jane.smith@example.com",
  "subject": "Green Architecture Consultation",
  "message": "I'm interested in sustainable building design for my new home. Could you provide more information about your services and pricing?",
  "status": "new"
}

### 6. Get contact by ID (replace 1 with actual ID)
GET http://localhost:3000/api/contacts/1

### 7. Update contact (replace 1 with actual ID)
PUT http://localhost:3000/api/contacts/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "full_name": "John Doe Updated",
  "phone": "+1234567890",
  "email": "john.updated@example.com",
  "subject": "Updated Subject",
  "message": "Updated message content",
  "status": "in_progress"
}

### 8. Update contact status only (replace 1 with actual ID)
PATCH http://localhost:3000/api/contacts/1/status
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "resolved"
}

### 9. Delete contact (replace 1 with actual ID)
DELETE http://localhost:3000/api/contacts/1

### 10. Test validation - Create contact without required fields (should fail)
POST http://localhost:3000/api/contacts
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "test@example.com"
}

